ssages containing all keywords: \'transport\', \'Error\', \'while\', \'dialing\' in close proximity.\\nCheck Log: Search for the keyword \'unavailable\' (case-insensitive) in log messages.\\nCheck Metric: Query the `pod_processes` metric for pods belonging to the \'adservice\' service and compare the p99 value during the fault window against the normal baseline.",\n    "Fault Type: adservice-getRandomAds-latency, rrt, rrt_max\\nSymptom: High JVM latency, JVM response delay, elevated request latency, and JVM slow response in adservice pod\\nRoot Cause: Component adservice-0 experienced adservice-getRandomAds-latency, rrt, rrt_max fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is adservice-0 (From Ground Truth, instance field, and present in logs with pod_name adservice-0). Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword adservice-getRandomAds-latency in Log, as seen in log messages about Byteman rule injection for latency (e.g., \'AdService-getRandomAds-latency-1749791449\'). Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword invocationtargetexception in Log, indicating Java reflection exception (e.g., \'java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\'). Step 4: Check Observation - Found keyword transformlistener in Log, via \'Transformer\' mentions related to Byteman agent transformation (e.g., \'org.jboss.byteman.agent.Transformer\'). Step 5: Derive Root Cause - Based on these features (latency rule injection, Java exceptions, agent transformation issues), determined cause is adservice-getRandomAds-latency, rrt, rrt_max fault leading to JVM latency.\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'adservice-getRandomAds-latency\' in application logs of pod adservice-0 during the fault timeframe.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'invocationtargetexception\' in error logs of pod adservice-0.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'transformlistener\' or \'Transformer\' in logs of pod adservice-0 to identify agent transformation issues.",\n    "Fault Type: pod_memory_working_set_bytes\\nSymptom: High memory usage, memory saturation, memory exhaustion, memory leak, memory stress in adservice pod\\nRoot Cause: Component [adservice-1] experienced [pod_memory_working_set_bytes] fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is [adservice-1] (From Ground Truth instance field) Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword [pod_memory_working_set_bytes] in Metric data (From GT key_observations) Step 3: Derive Root Cause - Based on above features, determined cause is [pod_memory_working_set_bytes] (From Ground Truth key_metrics)\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Metric: Search for metric keyword \'pod_memory_working_set_bytes\' in metric data to confirm it\'s being monitored\\nCheck Log: Search for log entries containing keyword \'http.resp.status\' with value \'302\' during fault timeframe"\n  ]\n}'}
